splay: inline-block;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"rich-link__read-more-text\" style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; font-family: \'Guardian Egyptian Web\', \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; display: inline-block; height: 1.875rem; line-height: 1.625rem; padding-left: 0.125rem; vertical-align: top; color: #005689;\">Read more</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</aside>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">But less than a fortnight later those expectations are being downgraded as Chinese sports fans and their&nbsp;&nbsp;come to terms with the fact that the Rio Games are unlikely to bear the fruits they had hoped for.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">China has struggled to replicate its triumphs at the&nbsp;&nbsp;and&nbsp;of 2008 and 2012. At the end of day 10, despite stunning successes in disciplines including diving and weightlifting,&nbsp;&nbsp;in the&nbsp;.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">That placed it not only behind the United States but also trailing historic foe Great Britain, with Team GB&rsquo;s athletes having won 16 gold medals to China&rsquo;s 15.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">&ldquo;You kidding me?&rdquo; the official English language Twitter account of Xinhua, China&rsquo;s government-controlled news agency,&nbsp;&nbsp;alongside a photograph of the unwelcome ranking. &ldquo;The country which has never finished above China is about to.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-tweet\" style=\"margin: 1rem 0px 0.75rem; position: relative; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/XHSports/status/765376240576376832\">\r\n<blockquote class=\"tweet twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-error\" style=\"margin: 1rem 1.25rem 0.75rem 0.625rem; display: inline-block; width: auto; max-width: 31.25rem; border-top: 0.0625rem dotted #bdbdbd; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.25rem; font-family: \'Guardian Text Sans Web\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; border-left-width: 0px; padding: 0.375rem 0px 0px; background-position: 0px 0.5rem !important; background-repeat: no-repeat;\" data-twitter-extracted-i1471360420523362277=\"true\"><img class=\"js-tweet-main-image tweet-main-image\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; width: 500px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Cp8pkJBWgAAD0tY.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"tweet-user\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-weight: bold; padding-left: 2.5rem; padding-bottom: 0.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0px; background-image: url(\'https://assets.guim.co.uk/images/twitter/ca807fd6567f678fc0981a4ab6904fbe/bird.svg\'); background-repeat: no-repeat;\">&mdash; Team China (@XHSports)</span>\r\n<p class=\"tweet-body\" dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">You kidding me? The country which has never finished above China is about to...</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">Chinese internet users expressed a mix of nonchalance and sour grapes at the country&rsquo;s fortunes in Brazil.</p>\r\n</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rich-link__read-more\" style=\"padding-left: 0.3125rem;\">\r\n<div class=\"rich-link__arrow\" style=\"height: 1.5rem; width: 1.5rem; display: inline-block;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"rich-link__read-more-text\" style=\"font-size: 0.875rem; font-family: \'Guardian Egyptian Web\', \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; display: inline-block; height: 1.875rem; line-height: 1.625rem; padding-left: 0.125rem; vertical-align: top; color: #005689;\">Read more</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</aside>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">&ldquo;It doesn&rsquo;t matter how many gold medals we have, as long as all the athletes can come home safely,&rdquo; one fan wrote on Weibo, China&rsquo;s answer to Twitter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">Another disenchanted commentator captured growing frustration among Chinese sports addicts. &ldquo;Rubbish Rio!&rdquo; they grumbled. &ldquo;Rubbish judges!&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">Team China&rsquo;s below-par performance has seen the country&rsquo;s state-controlled media change its tune over the Games, from a high-adrenaline samba to a wistful bossa nova.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">&ldquo;It will be hard for China to get more than 25 gold medals at this Olympics which would be the lowest number in the last five,&rdquo; journalist Yang Dawei conceded in&nbsp;in north-east China&rsquo;s Dalian Daily newspaper.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">After&nbsp;&nbsp;failed to win a single gold on day one of the Olympics, the usually bombastic Global Times offered a more measured appraisal of the country&rsquo;s chances.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">&ldquo;Public relax over medal tally,&rdquo; read the headline of&nbsp;&nbsp;which praised the public&rsquo;s &ldquo;remarkable tolerance to their national team&rsquo;s gold medal drought&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">He Wenyi, a Peking University sports expert, told the newspaper that as China had &ldquo;grown from a backward country to become the world&rsquo;s second largest economy, its people no longer need to use sporting prowess as a means to boost national confidence&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px;\">&ldquo;A gold medal at the Games is not as lustrous as before for the Chinese people,&rdquo; the academic was quoted as saying.</p>\r\n<div id=\"dfp-ad--inline1\" class=\"js-ad-slot ad-slot ad-slot--dfp ad-slot--inline ad-slot--inline1 ad-slot--rendered\" style=\"position: relative; z-index: 1010; overflow: initial; width: 18.75rem; margin: 0.25rem auto 0.75rem 1.25rem; min-height: 17.125rem; text-align: center; float: right; color: #333333; font-family: \'Guardian Text Egyptian Web\', Georgia, serif; font-size: medium; line-height: 24px; background-color: #f6f6f6;\" data-link-name=\"ad slot inline1\" data-test-id=\"ad-slot-inline1\" data-name=\"inline1\" data-mobile=\"1,1|300,250|fluid\" data-google-query-id=\"CKiCi9icxs4CFZasFgodzQcNFQ\">\r\n<div class=\"ad-slot__label\" style=\"font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.25rem; height: 1.5rem; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px